definition.value: Trianion of 4-phospho-D-erythronic acid arising from deprotonation of phosphate and carboxylic acid functions.
An optically active form of 1-piperideine-6-carboxylate having (S)-configuration.
A dicarboximide that is 3,4,5,6-tetrahydrophthalimide in which the hydrogen attached to the nitrogen is replaced by a p-bromophenyl group.
A monocarboxylic acid anion that is the conjugate base of N-acetyl-alpha-neuraminic acid.
An organophosphate oxoanion that is a trianion arising from deprotonation of the phosphate and carboxylic acid functions of 3-dehydro-L-gulonic acid 6-phosphate.
Conjugate base of CDP-choline(1+) arising from deprotonation of the diphosphate function.
An acyl-CoA(4-) obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate groups of any 2-hydroxy-3-methylacyl-CoA.
Tetraanion of 2-hydroxy-3-methylhexadecanoyl-CoA arising from deprotonation of phosphate and diphosphate functions.
An acyl-CoA(4-) that is the tetraanion of 2,3-dihydroxy-2,3-dihydrobenzoyl-CoA arising from deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate functions; major species at pH 7.3.
Pentaanion of cis-3,4-didehydroadipoyl-CoA arising from deprotonation of phosphate, diphosphate and carboxylic acid functions.
Tetraanion of cis-3,4-didehydroadipoyl-CoA semialdehyde arising from deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate functions.
Conjugate base of 1,2-dihydroxy-5-(methylthio)pent-1-en-3-one arising from deprotonation of the 2-hydroxy group.
Trianion of (9S,10S)-10-hydroxy-9-(phosphonooxy)octadecanoic acid arising from deprotonation of carboxylic acid and phosphate functions.
A hydroxy fatty acid anion that is the conjugate base of (S,S)-9,10-dihydroxyoctadecanoic acid.
An acyl-CoA(4-) that is the tetraanion of 3-hydroxycyclohexa-1,5-diene-1-carbonyl-CoA arising from deprotonation of phosphate and diphosphate functions.
A steroidal acyl-CoA(4-) that is the tetraanion of deoxycholoyl-CoA, arising from deprotonation of phosphate and diphosphate functions.
An acyl-CoA(4-) that is the tetraanion of phenylglyoxylyl-CoA arising from deprotonation of phosphate and diphosphate functions.
Conjugate base of sophoraflavanone B arising from deprotonation of the 7-hydroxy group.
Conjugate base of leachianone G arising from deprotonation of the 7-hydroxy group.
